Context and Defining Problem Statement¶

We have data for concrete with various with different values for various independent variables and corresponding concrete strngth (target variables).

Each row in the dataset containts values for how the concrete was made and what is corresponding concrete strength. There are 8 different attributes which contribute making the concrete for corresponding strength.

The objective is to develop linear regression model to predict the concrete strength using the data available and apply feature engineering and model tuning to obtain 80% to 95% of R2score.

The data for this project is available in file https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/concrete/compressive/.

Create a helper function to store metrics values in a dataframe for each model for comparison¶

In [79]:
modelMatrix = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['Method', 'R2 Score', 'MAE', 'MSE', 'RMSE', 'Max Error'])
def prepDF(modelName,y_test,y_pred):
    new_df = pd.DataFrame({'Method': [modelName], 
                        'R2 Score': [r2_score(y_test, y_pred)], 
                        'MAE': [mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)], 
                        'MSE': [mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)],
                        'RMSE': [mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)**0.5],
                        'Max Error': [max_error(y_test, y_pred)] })
    return new_df

We can make following observations based on various models and their accuracies:

  • We can note that simple linear regression model returned very low result. It was being very simple and was not able to capture the enough variance hence low accuracy.
  • Once we implemented feature engineering using polynomial terms then we can see the improvement in the resultant model accuracy.
  • Once we implemented regularization using Ridge and Lasso then we can see that both returned almost similar result but there was not much improvement in the accuracy.
  • More advance models like Decision Tree and other ensemble model helped achieving better accuracy. Bagging Regressor was able to deliver the best accuracy among all generted models.
  • Implmented GridSearchCV and RandomizedSearhCV however couldn't get much improvement using the techniques.
